Conventional commit
feat: A new feature introduced to the application.
fix: A patch or bug fix for the codebase.
docs: Changes to the documentation (e.g., README updates).
refactor: Code changes that neither fix a bug nor add a feature.
style: Formatting changes, missing semicolons, etc. (no impact on code logic).
test: Adding or correcting tests.
chore: Updating build tasks, package manager configs, or auxiliary tools (e.g., CI/CD workflow updates).